<br>
They said in the patch message that a duo will get better exp than it currently does. This does set a limit for how much baseline exp in pop zones can be decreased.<br>
<br>
For example we will take a PoP mob worth 100 exp. 2 person group, both same level.<br>
<br>
Currently a group of 2 get 100 exp, then modified by 2% for group bonus. Now they got 100*1.02 or 102 exp. This is split evenly between them. So they gain 102/2 = 51 exp each.<br>
<br>
51 exp each is the bare minimum they should get post patch.<br>
<br>
Post patch the exp bonus for a two man group is 1.2. Post patch the monster is worth X exp.<br>
<br>
We know that 1.2X/2&gt;51<br>
then<br>
1.2X&gt;51*2<br>
1.2X&gt;102<br>
X&gt;102/1.2<br>
X&gt;85<br>
<br>
So the maximum exp nerf for monster exp is 15%.<br>
<br>
Lets assume that they nerf monster exp the max amount. How will this affect a full group of 6 compared to now?<br>
<br>
Currently a group of 6 get 100*1.2/6=20 exp each. (20% bonus for full group.)<br>
<br>
Post patch they get 85*1.8/5=30.6 exp each.<br>
<br>
So post patch a full group should gain 50% more exp than it currently does per kill in the WORST CASE SCENARIO!<br>
<br>
