<br>
1) This change is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>long</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> overdue.  This should have been in the game from day 1.  People have been asking for this from day 1.  Why in god's name were they so resistant to it?  For a game that emphasizes group cooperation, it never should have been the case that increasing the size of your group slowed your rate of advancement.  It made no sense that bards... a class designed from the ground up to be a group supporter... earned hella better XP dicking around by themselves than they did with a group.  This change went in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>way</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> too late for me to toss any Kudos in SOE's direction, but I'm glad they finally came to their damn senses.<br>
<br>
2) For people talking about soloing in a group... there is a fixed range at which the game will treat you as though you're in a group.  Basically, if you get the message &quot;you earn party experience&quot; when a monster dies you're in range, but if you get the message &quot;you earn some experience&quot; you're out of range.  If you make a 6 person druid group, and everyone goes kiting in different parts of the zone, you're not gonna earn any extra.  You'd have to kite so close together to earn the group bonus that your monsters would keep aggroing on other druids and stuff (unless you're kiting non-social non-aggressive mobs (giant snakes, as an example)).<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aubie>Aubie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/28/03 2:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> Three words: About goddamn time!<br>
